<inglise> No person may be a manager of a grouping if: </inglise>
<eesti> Huvigrupi tegevjuhiks ei v&otilde;i olla isik, kes </eesti>
<inglise> - by virtue of the law applicable to him, or </inglise>
<eesti> - tema suhtes kohaldatava seaduse j&auml;rgi v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - by virtue of the internal law of the State in which the grouping has its official address, or </inglise>
<eesti> - selle riigi &otilde;iguse j&auml;rgi, kus on huvigrupi asukoht, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - following a judicial or administrative decision made or recognized in a Member State he may not belong to the administrative or management body of a company, may not manage an undertaking or may not act as manager of a European Economic Interest Grouping. </inglise>
<eesti> - liikmesriigis tehtud v&otilde;i tunnustatud kohtu- v&otilde;i haldusotsuse j&auml;rgi ei v&otilde;i kuuluda &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhtorganisse, juhtida ettev&otilde;tet v&otilde;i tegutseda Euroopa majandushuvigrupi tegevjuhina. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> A Member State may, in the case of groupings registered at their registries pursuant to Article 6, provide that legal persons may be managers on condition that such legal persons designate one or more natural persons, whose particulars shall be the subject of the filing provisions of Article 7 (d) to represent them. </inglise>
