<inglise> Such expulsion may occur only by the decision of a court to which joint application has been made by a majority of the other members, unless otherwise provided by the contract for the formation of a grouping. </inglise>
<eesti> Selline v&auml;ljaheitmine v&otilde;ib toimuda &uuml;ksnes kohtuotsusega, millekohase taotluse peab esitama &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud liikmete enamus, kui asutamislepingus pole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 28 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 28 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A member of a grouping shall cease to belong to it on death or when he no longer complies with the conditions laid down in Article 4 (1). </inglise>
<eesti> Huvigrupi liikme liikmelisus l&otilde;peb tema surma korral v&otilde;i siis, kui ta ei vasta enam artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise> In addition, a Member State may provide, for the purposes of its liquidation, winding up, insolvency or cessation of payments laws, that a member shall cease to be a member of any grouping at the moment determined by those laws. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks v&otilde;ib liikmesriik likvideerimist, l&otilde;petamist, maksej&otilde;uetust v&otilde;i maksete lakkamist k&auml;sitlevate seaduste raames s&auml;testada, et huvigrupi liikme liikmelisus l&otilde;peb nendes seadustes kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajal. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In the event of the death of a natural person who is a member of a grouping, no person may become a member in his place except under the conditions laid down in the contract for the formation of the grouping or, failing that, with the unanimous agreement of the remaining members. </inglise>
